Since Claude remembers the context, refinements can be very short — you don't need to restate the task. Get an answer, and steer it with a single phrase:

- **"Rewrite it shorter"** — will condense the text while keeping the essence;
- **"Simpler"** — will remove complex terms and jargon;
- **"Format it as a list"** or "make it a table" — will change the structure;
- **"Expand the second point in more detail"** — will go deeper into a specific spot;
- **"Give me 3 more options"** — will offer alternatives;
- **"Not that. I need it for 10-year-old kids"** — will reorient the whole answer.

Notice the last example: even saying "not that" is helpful. Explain what exactly is wrong, and the next version will be closer to the goal.
